ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Age in years
Visit name
Version/code of assessment
Phlebotomy: difference in minutes between baseline (Enrollment Visit) and follow-up blood draw times
Phlebotomy: which draw(s) blood obtained at
Notes: 0= No sample collected at visit; 1= Sample at 1st collection only; 2= Sample at 2nd collection only; 3= Sample at 1st and 2nd collections

ElementDescription: Phlebotomy: which draw(s) citrate obtained at

ElementDescription: Phlebotomy: which draw(s) serum obtained at

ElementDescription: Phlebotomy: completeness of recent surgery information
Notes: 0= Surgery info thru 12 mo before MRI date; 1= Surgery info only thru 2 mo before MRI date; 2= 12-m info thru prescreen date, no planned surgery; 3= 12-m info thru prescreen date, surgery planned; 4= 2-m info thru prescreen date, no planned surgery; 5= 2-m info thru prescreen date, surgery planned; 6= Surgery info not collected; 7= Surgery info thru 12 mo as of clinic visit
